data.name: Junction.ToolTip
data.value: The function of a junction is to reference a target directory, unlike ahard link which points to a file. Junctions can be created to link directories located on different partitions or volume, but only locally on the same computer.

data.name: HardLink.ToolTip
data.value: A hard link is a file that represents another file on the same volume without actually duplicating the dataof that file. More than one hard link can be created to point at the same file. Hard links cannot link to afile that is on a different partition, volume or drive.
